    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      405.56,
      526.32,
      418.6
    ],
    "text": "The Accused-Appellant (hereinafter referred to as \u2018the Appellant\u2019) was indicted before the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      425.36,
      335.42,
      438.4
    ],
    "text": "High Court of Trincomalee on the following charge,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      451.16,
      529.87,
      464.2
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThat on or about 28.05.2017 within the Jurisdiction of this Court in Muthur, you",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      470.98,
      529.81,
      484.02
    ],
    "text": "in order to fulfill your carnal lust, had placed your hand on the female organ of",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      490.9,
      529.85,
      503.94
    ],
    "text": "Umakandan Dilakshani , that is you having groped the sexual organ with your",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      510.7,
      529.95,
      523.74
    ],
    "text": "hands of the above named Umakandan Dilakshani ,and that you have thereby",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      530.5,
      529.94,
      543.54
    ],
    "text": "committed an offence of a grave sexual abuse punishable under Section 365 (b) (2)",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      550.3,
      529.74,
      563.34
    ],
    "text": "(b) of the Ceylon Penal Code as amended by Act No 22 of 1995, Act No 29 of 1998",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      570.22,
      234.03,
      583.26
    ],
    "text": "and Act No 16 of 2006.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      601.3,
      526.17,
      614.34
    ],
    "text": "On 14.07.2020, State Counsel led the evidence of PW1, Umakandan Dilakshani. In her",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      621.1,
      526.19,
      634.14
    ],
    "text": "testimony, she described how the appellant molested her and further stated that on the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      640.9,
      526.18,
      653.94
    ],
    "text": "same day, the appellant also molested two other minors, Karshika and Nikshida. After",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      660.85,
      526.24,
      673.89
    ],
    "text": "her evidence concluded, the trial was adjourned to 03.09.2020. In the meantime, on",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      680.65,
      526.18,
      693.69
    ],
    "text": "24.08.2020, the learned High Court Judge heard case No. 1015/20 against the same",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      700.45,
      526.49,
      713.49
    ],
    "text": "appellant, during which Karshika again gave evidence and narrated the same story",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      720.37,
      249.72,
      733.41
    ],
    "text": "elicited by the PW 01 in this case.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      779.14,
      327.38,
      805.78
    ],
    "text": "Page 3 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      71.91,
      526.45,
      84.95
    ],
    "text": "Thereafter, both cases were taken simultaneously; evidence was recorded on the same",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      91.73,
      526.42,
      104.77
    ],
    "text": "date, and both judgments were delivered on the same day. Our courts have consistently",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      111.65,
      526.17,
      124.69
    ],
    "text": "held that consolidating trials against a single accused for similar offences is",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      131.45,
      526.12,
      144.49
    ],
    "text": "impermissible, and such a conviction is considered illegal. I am mindful of the following",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      151.25,
      215.88,
      164.29
    ],
    "text": "judgements in this regard.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      180.17,
      429.38,
      193.21
    ],
    "text": "The King v. Mendis, 16 NLR 252 at page 253, Lascelles C.J held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      209.93,
      498.31,
      222.97
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThere is no objection, as regards joinder of counts, to any one of these",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      229.73,
      498.37,
      242.77
    ],
    "text": "indictments, but by some blunder, which has not been explained, the accused",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      249.65,
      498.29,
      262.69
    ],
    "text": "was tried simultaneously on all indictments and was convicted on all the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      269.6,
      291.75,
      282.64
    ],
    "text": "charges in each of the indictments.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      299.48,
      164.88,
      312.52
    ],
    "text": "\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026..",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      329.12,
      498.3,
      342.16
    ],
    "text": "Further, it is impossible to hold that the accused was not prejudiced by the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      349.04,
      498.27,
      362.08
    ],
    "text": "course taken. His position is obviously worse than it would have been had",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      368.84,
      498.24,
      381.88
    ],
    "text": "he been tried on any one of the indictments. That this is so is apparent by",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      388.64,
      498.47,
      401.68
    ],
    "text": "comparing the position in which the accused would have been if he had been",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      408.44,
      498.28,
      421.48
    ],
    "text": "tried on one indictment only with that in which he was placed at the trial.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      428.36,
      498.34,
      441.4
    ],
    "text": "If, for example, only for giving false evidence at the inquest, he would",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      448.16,
      498.56,
      461.2
    ],
    "text": "obviously have been in a better position than he was when two other",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      467.98,
      498.35,
      481.02
    ],
    "text": "indictments were before the Court charging him with having made false",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      487.9,
      426.5,
      500.94
    ],
    "text": "statements about the same matter on four different occasions.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      527.5,
      498.27,
      540.54
    ],
    "text": "In my opinion, the simultaneous trial of these three indictments is a fatal",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      547.3,
      498.31,
      560.34
    ],
    "text": "irregularity, and I set aside the conviction and acquit and discharge the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      567.34,
      161.52,
      580.38
    ],
    "text": "accused.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      596.98,
      474.05,
      610.02
    ],
    "text": "The King v. Podi Appuhamy, 29 NLR 102, at page 105, Schneidex, J held that;",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      624.82,
      529.79,
      637.86
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThere is another reason for which their convictions might be set aside, and that",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      644.77,
      529.81,
      657.81
    ],
    "text": "is that both the accused were tried together although upon separate indictments.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      664.57,
      529.82,
      677.61
    ],
    "text": "The charges were different.. But that procedure, it might be argued, has not",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      684.37,
      529.82,
      697.41
    ],
    "text": "prejudiced them. Even so I think that the irregularity was of such a grave nature",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      704.29,
      529.83,
      717.33
    ],
    "text": "that the convictions should be set aside on that ground too. If they had been set",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      724.09,
      529.8,
      737.13
    ],
    "text": "aside on that ground, the proper order would have been for a fresh trial. I prefer",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      743.89,
      437.69,
      756.93
    ],
    "text": "therefore to rest my decision on the other reasons given by me.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      779.14,
      327.38,
      805.78
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      71.91,
      526.14,
      84.95
    ],
    "text": "In the instant case, the appellant was tried before the same judge on similar offences.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      91.73,
      526.18,
      104.77
    ],
    "text": "During the proceedings, the judge heard witness testimony regarding the incidents, and",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      111.65,
      526.48,
      124.69
    ],
    "text": "before reaching his conclusion, appears to have reasoned that since the appellant was",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      131.45,
      526.33,
      144.49
    ],
    "text": "charged with similar offences, he must therefore be guilty. Before evidence been concluded",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      151.25,
      342.26,
      164.29
    ],
    "text": "he opined that the Appellant is guilty of the offence.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      182.33,
      526.11,
      195.37
    ],
    "text": "In criminal trials, the prosecution is generally restricted from presenting evidence of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      202.25,
      526.22,
      215.29
    ],
    "text": "accused\u2019s bad character. This principle is embodied in Section 54 of the Evidence",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      222.05,
      526.49,
      235.09
    ],
    "text": "Ordinance, which limits the admissibility of such evidence to prevent undue prejudice",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      241.85,
      177.93,
      254.89
    ],
    "text": "against the accused.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      272.96,
      529.89,
      286.0
    ],
    "text": "54. In criminal proceedings the fact that the accused person has a bad character is",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      292.76,
      529.81,
      305.8
    ],
    "text": "irrelevant, unless evidence has been given that he has a good character, in which",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      312.68,
      240.99,
      325.72
    ],
    "text": "case it becomes relevant.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      343.76,
      529.96,
      356.8
    ],
    "text": "Explanation 1. - This section does not apply to cases in which the bad character of",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      363.56,
      287.07,
      376.6
    ],
    "text": "any person is itself a fact in issue.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      394.64,
      529.89,
      407.68
    ],
    "text": "Explanation 2. - A previous conviction is relevant as evidence of bad character in",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      414.44,
      165.84,
      427.48
    ],
    "text": "such case.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      443.36,
      526.49,
      456.4
    ],
    "text": "I am mindful to refer to the The Law of Evidence, Volume I, E.R.S.R. Coomaraswamy, at",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      463.18,
      126.45,
      476.22
    ],
    "text": "page 684,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      491.02,
      506.19,
      504.06
    ],
    "text": "\u201c13C.3. Generally Bad Character is Irrelevant in Criminal Cases \u2013 Section 54",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      510.82,
      375.48,
      523.86
    ],
    "text": "(i) Section 54 - Bad character is generally irrelevant",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      530.74,
      529.82,
      543.78
    ],
    "text": "Section 54 lays down the general rule that in criminal proceedings, the fact that",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      550.54,
      529.79,
      563.58
    ],
    "text": "the accused has a bad character is irrelevant, except in the exceptional cases",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      570.34,
      211.71,
      583.38
    ],
    "text": "mentioned therein.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      617.98,
      529.81,
      631.02
    ],
    "text": "65 Evidence may not be given of the accused's previous convictions or misconduct",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      637.9,
      529.73,
      650.94
    ],
    "text": "on other occasions for the purpose of supporting an argument that he is the kind",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      657.73,
      529.8,
      670.77
    ],
    "text": "of person who would commit the crime charged. As Wigmore puts it, \"the rule,",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      677.53,
      529.94,
      690.57
    ],
    "text": "then, firmly and universally established in policy and tradition is that the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      697.45,
      436.49,
      710.49
    ],
    "text": "prosecution may not initially attack the defendant's character\"",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      745.09,
      291.27,
      758.13
    ],
    "text": "(i) Principle underlying the section",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      779.14,
      327.38,
      805.78
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 6",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      91.73,
      529.82,
      104.77
    ],
    "text": "The desire for fair play and even indulgence has led to this rule. The principle",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      111.65,
      529.8,
      124.69
    ],
    "text": "underlying the rule is that hardship is possible, as evidence of bad character may",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      131.45,
      529.78,
      144.49
    ],
    "text": "lead the mind of the judge or jury away from the point to be decided, namely, the",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      151.25,
      529.86,
      164.29
    ],
    "text": "guilt or innocence of the accused person in regard to the particular offence with",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      171.05,
      370.82,
      184.09
    ],
    "text": "which he is charged. The main ground is prejudice.",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      210.77,
      526.45,
      223.81
    ],
    "text": "It is pertinent to refer to the passage in \u201cthe proof of guilt\u201d, Third Editition, Glanville",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      230.57,
      172.17,
      243.61
    ],
    "text": "Williams, page 212",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      278.36,
      418.97,
      291.4
    ],
    "text": "THE EXCLUSION OF CHARACTER AND CONVICTIONS",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      326.0,
      529.93,
      339.04
    ],
    "text": "The feature of the English system that most puzzles and intrigues foreign lawyers",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      345.8,
      529.85,
      358.84
    ],
    "text": "is that the prosecution are generally not allowed to give evidence of the accused's",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      365.6,
      529.92,
      378.64
    ],
    "text": "bad character or previous convictions in order to help establish that he committed",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      385.52,
      529.84,
      398.56
    ],
    "text": "the crime in question. Such evidence can in general be given only after conviction",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      405.32,
      530.0,
      418.36
    ],
    "text": "in order todetermine punishment. In many other countries, on the other hand, this",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      425.12,
      529.76,
      438.16
    ],
    "text": "evidence is the very first to be adduced at the trial. On the face of it the English",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      445.04,
      529.94,
      458.08
    ],
    "text": "system might seem to be over-lenient to the accused, because we do in everyday",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      464.86,
      529.78,
      477.9
    ],
    "text": "life attach importance to the question whether the person whose worth we are",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      484.66,
      529.78,
      497.7
    ],
    "text": "assessing has a criminal record or not. One reason for the English rule is that",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      504.58,
      529.86,
      517.62
    ],
    "text": "evidence of general evil propensity is thought to widen the issues of the trial so",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      524.38,
      529.77,
      537.42
    ],
    "text": "immensely as to be unfair to the accused. Even the notorious Judge Jeffreys may",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      544.18,
      529.72,
      557.22
    ],
    "text": "be found to say, in Hampden's case, that \"to rake into the whole course of a man's",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      563.98,
      529.95,
      577.02
    ],
    "text": "life is very hard\"; and Mr. Justice Withins said on the same occasion: \"We would",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      583.9,
      529.94,
      596.94
    ],
    "text": "not suffer any raking into men's course of life, to pick up evidence that they cannot",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      603.7,
      529.78,
      616.74
    ],
    "text": "be prepared to answer to.\" This reason would not in itself explain why we exclude",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      623.5,
      529.98,
      636.54
    ],
    "text": "evidence of previous offences which are admitted by the defendant, or of previous",
    "fonts": [
      "Century"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      107.3,
      643.45,
      529.91,
      656.49
    ],
